Note:
Comprehensive Test Suite for Distributed Memory Module

Tests all functionality of the distributed memory management system including:
- Cross-system memory coordination and synchronization
- Distributed memory allocation and deallocation
- Network-based memory sharing and communication
- Fault tolerance and recovery mechanisms
- Distributed garbage collection coordination
- Performance optimization for distributed scenarios
- Security and access control for distributed memory
- Load balancing and resource management
- Production-ready enterprise distributed memory scenarios
:End Note

Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/memory/distributed_memory" as DistributedMemory
Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/utilities/common" as Common

Note: Test Configuration Constants
Let TEST_NODE_COUNT be 3
Let TEST_MEMORY_BLOCK_SIZE be 1024
Let TEST_NETWORK_LATENCY_MS be 10
Let TEST_DISTRIBUTED_OPERATIONS be 50

Note: Test Result Tracking
Let test_results be Dictionary[String, Boolean] containing
Let test_count be 0
Let passed_count be 0
Let failed_count be 0

Note: Helper Functions for Testing

Process called "run_test" that takes test_name as String and test_function as Function returns Boolean:
    Set test_count to test_count plus 1
    
    Try:
        Display message "Running test: " plus test_name
        Let result be test_function()
        
        If result:
            Set passed_count to passed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to true
            Display message "  ✓ PASS: " plus test_name
        Otherwise:
            Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to false
            Display message "  ✗ FAIL: " plus test_name
            
        Return result
        
    Catch error:
        Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
        Set test_results[test_name] to false
        Display message "  ✗ ERROR: " plus test_name plus " - " plus error.message
        Return false

Process called "assert_true" that takes condition as Boolean and message as String returns Boolean:
    If not condition:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "assert_equal" that takes actual as Any and expected as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is not equal to expected:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected: " plus expected
        Display message "    Actual: " plus actual
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "assert_not_null" that takes value as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If value is null:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "create_mock_distributed_node" that takes node_id as String returns DistributedMemory.DistributedNode:
    Return DistributedMemory.DistributedNode with:
        node_id as node_id
        address as "127.0.0." plus node_id
        port as (8000 plus node_id.to_integer())
        available_memory as 1073741824
        used_memory as 0
        status as "active"
        last_heartbeat as Common.get_current_time_ms()
        metadata as dictionary containing

Note: Unit Tests for Distributed Memory Context

Process called "test_create_distributed_context" returns Boolean:
    Let config be DistributedMemory.DistributedConfig with:
        cluster_name as "test_cluster"
        replication_factor as 2
        consistency_level as "strong"
        heartbeat_interval_ms as 1000
        timeout_ms as 5000
        
    Let distributed_context be DistributedMemory.create_distributed_context with config as config
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as distributed_context and message as "Distributed context should be created"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as distributed_context.config.cluster_name and expected as "test_cluster" and message as "Cluster name should be set"
    Let result3 be assert_equal with actual as distributed_context.config.replication_factor and expected as 2 and message as "Replication factor should be set"
    Let result4 be assert_not_null with value as distributed_context.coordinator and message as "Coordinator should be initialized"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_join_distributed_cluster" returns Boolean:
    Let distributed_context be DistributedMemory.create_distributed_context with config as DistributedMemory.default_config
    
    Note: Create test nodes
    Let nodes be list containing
    For i from 1 to TEST_NODE_COUNT:
        Let node be create_mock_distributed_node with node_id as i.to_string()
        Let nodes be nodes with node added
    
    Note: Join cluster with nodes
    For node in nodes:
        Let join_result be DistributedMemory.join_cluster with context as distributed_context and node as node
        
        If not assert_true with condition as join_result and message as "Node should join cluster successfully":
            Return false
    
    Let result1 be assert_equal with actual as distributed_context.active_nodes.length and expected as TEST_NODE_COUNT and message as "All nodes should be active"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as distributed_context.is_cluster_healthy and message as "Cluster should be healthy"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: Unit Tests for Distributed Allocation

Process called "test_distributed_memory_allocation" returns Boolean:
    Let distributed_context be DistributedMemory.create_distributed_context with config as DistributedMemory.default_config
    
    Note: Setup cluster with nodes
    For i from 1 to TEST_NODE_COUNT:
        Let node be create_mock_distributed_node with node_id as i.to_string()
        DistributedMemory.join_cluster with context as distributed_context and node as node
    
    Let allocation_request be DistributedMemory.AllocationRequest with:
        size as TEST_MEMORY_BLOCK_SIZE
        alignment as 8
        replication_level as 2
        locality_preference as "any"
        timeout_ms as 3000
        
    Let distributed_pointer be DistributedMemory.allocate_distributed with context as distributed_context and request as allocation_request
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as distributed_pointer and message as "Distributed allocation should succeed"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as distributed_pointer.size and expected as TEST_MEMORY_BLOCK_SIZE and message as "Allocation size should match"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as (distributed_pointer.replica_count is greater than or equal to 2) and message as "Should have requested replicas"
    Let result4 be assert_not_null with value as distributed_pointer.primary_node and message as "Primary node should be assigned"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_distributed_memory_replication" returns Boolean:
    Let distributed_context be DistributedMemory.create_distributed_context with config as DistributedMemory.default_config
    
    Note: Setup cluster
    For i from 1 to TEST_NODE_COUNT:
        Let node be create_mock_distributed_node with node_id as i.to_string()
        DistributedMemory.join_cluster with context as distributed_context and node as node
    
    Let allocation_request be DistributedMemory.AllocationRequest with:
        size as 512
        alignment as 8
        replication_level as 3
        consistency_level as "strong"
        
    Let distributed_pointer be DistributedMemory.allocate_distributed with context as distributed_context and request as allocation_request
    
    Note: Verify replication
    Let replication_info be DistributedMemory.get_replication_info with pointer as distributed_pointer
    
    Let result1 be assert_equal with actual as replication_info.replica_count and expected as 3 and message as "Should have 3 replicas"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (replication_info.replicas.length is equal to 3) and message as "Replica list should contain 3 nodes"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as replication_info.is_consistent and message as "Replicas should be consistent"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: Unit Tests for Distributed Synchronization

Process called "test_distributed_memory_consistency" returns Boolean:
    Let distributed_context be DistributedMemory.create_distributed_context with config as DistributedMemory.default_config
    
    Note: Setup cluster
    For i from 1 to TEST_NODE_COUNT:
        Let node be create_mock_distributed_node with node_id as i.to_string()
        DistributedMemory.join_cluster with context as distributed_context and node as node
    
    Let allocation_request be DistributedMemory.AllocationRequest with:
        size as 256
        replication_level as 2
        consistency_level as "strong"
        
    Let distributed_pointer be DistributedMemory.allocate_distributed with context as distributed_context and request as allocation_request
    
    Note: Write data to distributed memory
    Let write_data be "test_data_consistency_check"
    Let write_result be DistributedMemory.write_distributed with pointer as distributed_pointer and data as write_data
    
    Note: Read from different replicas
    Let read_results be list containing
    For replica in distributed_pointer.replicas:
        Let read_data be DistributedMemory.read_from_replica with pointer as distributed_pointer and replica as replica
        Let read_results be read_results with read_data added
    
    Note: All reads should return same data
    Let all_consistent be true
    For read_data in read_results:
        If read_data is not equal to write_data:
            Set all_consistent to false
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as write_result and message as "Distributed write should succeed"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as all_consistent and message as "All replicas should have consistent data"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_distributed_locking" returns Boolean:
    Let distributed_context be DistributedMemory.create_distributed_context with config as DistributedMemory.default_config
    
    Note: Setup cluster
    For i from 1 to TEST_NODE_COUNT:
        Let node be create_mock_distributed_node with node_id as i.to_string()
        DistributedMemory.join_cluster with context as distributed_context and node as node
    
    Let lock_id be "test_distributed_lock"
    Let lock_timeout_ms be 2000
    
    Note: Acquire lock from first node
    Let lock1 be DistributedMemory.acquire_distributed_lock with context as distributed_context and lock_id as lock_id and timeout_ms as lock_timeout_ms
    
    Note: Try to acquire same lock from second node (should fail)
    Let lock2 be DistributedMemory.acquire_distributed_lock with context as distributed_context and lock_id as lock_id and timeout_ms as 100
    
    Note: Release first lock
    Let release_result be DistributedMemory.release_distributed_lock with context as distributed_context and lock as lock1
    
    Note: Now second acquisition should succeed
    Let lock3 be DistributedMemory.acquire_distributed_lock with context as distributed_context and lock_id as lock_id and timeout_ms as lock_timeout_ms
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as lock1 and message as "First lock acquisition should succeed"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (lock2 is null) and message as "Second lock acquisition should fail"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as release_result and message as "Lock release should succeed"
    Let result4 be assert_not_null with value as lock3 and message as "Lock acquisition after release should succeed"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Note: Unit Tests for Fault Tolerance

Process called "test_node_failure_handling" returns Boolean:
    Let distributed_context be DistributedMemory.create_distributed_context with config as DistributedMemory.default_config
    
    Note: Setup cluster
    Let nodes be list containing
    For i from 1 to TEST_NODE_COUNT:
        Let node be create_mock_distributed_node with node_id as i.to_string()
        DistributedMemory.join_cluster with context as distributed_context and node as node
        Let nodes be nodes with node added
    
    Note: Allocate memory with replication
    Let allocation_request be DistributedMemory.AllocationRequest with:
        size as 512
        replication_level as 2
        
    Let distributed_pointer be DistributedMemory.allocate_distributed with context as distributed_context and request as allocation_request
    
    Note: Simulate node failure
    Let failed_node be nodes[0]
    DistributedMemory.simulate_node_failure with context as distributed_context and node as failed_node
    
    Note: System should detect failure and recover
    Let recovery_result be DistributedMemory.trigger_failure_recovery with context as distributed_context
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as recovery_result and message as "Failure recovery should succeed"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (distributed_context.active_nodes.length is equal to (TEST_NODE_COUNT minus 1)) and message as "Failed node should be removed"
    Let result3 be assert_not_null with value as distributed_pointer and message as "Existing allocations should remain valid"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Process called "test_distributed_garbage_collection" returns Boolean:
    Let distributed_context be DistributedMemory.create_distributed_context with config as DistributedMemory.default_config
    
    Note: Setup cluster
    For i from 1 to TEST_NODE_COUNT:
        Let node be create_mock_distributed_node with node_id as i.to_string()
        DistributedMemory.join_cluster with context as distributed_context and node as node
    
    Note: Allocate and then free memory to create garbage
    Let pointers_to_free be list containing
    For i from 0 to 9:
        Let allocation_request be DistributedMemory.AllocationRequest with size as 128 and replication_level as 1
        Let pointer be DistributedMemory.allocate_distributed with context as distributed_context and request as allocation_request
        Let pointers_to_free be pointers_to_free with pointer added
    
    Note: Free some pointers
    For i from 0 to 4:
        DistributedMemory.free_distributed with context as distributed_context and pointer as pointers_to_free[i]
    
    Note: Trigger distributed garbage collection
    Let gc_result be DistributedMemory.trigger_distributed_gc with context as distributed_context
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as gc_result.success and message as "Distributed GC should succeed"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (gc_result.reclaimed_memory is greater than 0) and message as "Some memory should be reclaimed"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as (gc_result.participating_nodes is equal to TEST_NODE_COUNT) and message as "All nodes should participate in GC"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: Performance Tests

Process called "test_distributed_allocation_performance" returns Boolean:
    Let distributed_context be DistributedMemory.create_distributed_context with config as DistributedMemory.default_config
    
    Note: Setup cluster
    For i from 1 to TEST_NODE_COUNT:
        Let node be create_mock_distributed_node with node_id as i.to_string()
        DistributedMemory.join_cluster with context as distributed_context and node as node
    
    Let start_time be Common.get_current_time_ms()
    
    Note: Perform multiple distributed allocations
    For i from 0 to (TEST_DISTRIBUTED_OPERATIONS minus 1):
        Let allocation_request be DistributedMemory.AllocationRequest with:
            size as 64
            replication_level as 1
            
        Let pointer be DistributedMemory.allocate_distributed with context as distributed_context and request as allocation_request
    
    Let end_time be Common.get_current_time_ms()
    Let total_time_ms be end_time minus start_time
    Let avg_time_per_allocation be total_time_ms divided by TEST_DISTRIBUTED_OPERATIONS
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (avg_time_per_allocation is less than 50.0) and message as "Average distributed allocation time should be reasonable"
    
    Return result1

Process called "test_network_communication_performance" returns Boolean:
    Let distributed_context be DistributedMemory.create_distributed_context with config as DistributedMemory.default_config
    
    Note: Setup cluster
    For i from 1 to TEST_NODE_COUNT:
        Let node be create_mock_distributed_node with node_id as i.to_string()
        DistributedMemory.join_cluster with context as distributed_context and node as node
    
    Let start_time be Common.get_current_time_ms()
    
    Note: Test network communication performance
    For i from 0 to 19:
        Let message be DistributedMemory.NetworkMessage with:
            type as "heartbeat"
            payload as "test_data"
            timestamp as Common.get_current_time_ms()
            
        DistributedMemory.broadcast_message with context as distributed_context and message as message
    
    Let end_time be Common.get_current_time_ms()
    Let total_time_ms be end_time minus start_time
    Let avg_time_per_message be total_time_ms divided by 20
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (avg_time_per_message is less than 20.0) and message as "Average message broadcast time should be fast"
    
    Return result1

Note: Security Tests

Process called "test_distributed_access_control" returns Boolean:
    Let distributed_context be DistributedMemory.create_distributed_context with config as DistributedMemory.default_config
    
    Note: Setup secure cluster
    For i from 1 to TEST_NODE_COUNT:
        Let node be create_mock_distributed_node with node_id as i.to_string()
        DistributedMemory.join_cluster with context as distributed_context and node as node
    
    Note: Create allocation with access control
    Let allocation_request be DistributedMemory.AllocationRequest with:
        size as 256
        access_control as "restricted"
        allowed_operations as ["read", "write"]
        
    Let distributed_pointer be DistributedMemory.allocate_distributed with context as distributed_context and request as allocation_request
    
    Note: Test authorized access
    Let authorized_read be DistributedMemory.read_distributed with pointer as distributed_pointer and credentials as "valid_auth"
    
    Note: Test unauthorized access
    Let unauthorized_read be DistributedMemory.read_distributed with pointer as distributed_pointer and credentials as "invalid_auth"
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as authorized_read and message as "Authorized access should succeed"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (unauthorized_read is null) and message as "Unauthorized access should be denied"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: Error Handling Tests

Process called "test_network_partition_handling" returns Boolean:
    Let distributed_context be DistributedMemory.create_distributed_context with config as DistributedMemory.default_config
    
    Note: Setup cluster
    For i from 1 to TEST_NODE_COUNT:
        Let node be create_mock_distributed_node with node_id as i.to_string()
        DistributedMemory.join_cluster with context as distributed_context and node as node
    
    Note: Simulate network partition
    DistributedMemory.simulate_network_partition with context as distributed_context and partitioned_nodes as [1, 2]
    
    Note: Test system behavior during partition
    Let allocation_request be DistributedMemory.AllocationRequest with size as 128
    Let allocation_result be DistributedMemory.allocate_distributed with context as distributed_context and request as allocation_request
    
    Note: System should either succeed or fail gracefully
    Let handled_gracefully be (allocation_result is not null) or (DistributedMemory.get_last_error() is not null)
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as handled_gracefully and message as "Network partition should be handled gracefully"
    
    Return result1

Process called "test_distributed_memory_corruption_detection" returns Boolean:
    Let distributed_context be DistributedMemory.create_distributed_context with config as DistributedMemory.default_config
    
    Note: Setup cluster with checksum verification
    For i from 1 to TEST_NODE_COUNT:
        Let node be create_mock_distributed_node with node_id as i.to_string()
        DistributedMemory.join_cluster with context as distributed_context and node as node
    
    Let allocation_request be DistributedMemory.AllocationRequest with:
        size as 256
        replication_level as 2
        enable_checksum as true
        
    Let distributed_pointer be DistributedMemory.allocate_distributed with context as distributed_context and request as allocation_request
    
    Note: Write data
    Let original_data be "important_data"
    DistributedMemory.write_distributed with pointer as distributed_pointer and data as original_data
    
    Note: Simulate corruption on one replica
    DistributedMemory.simulate_replica_corruption with pointer as distributed_pointer and replica_index as 0
    
    Note: System should detect corruption
    Let corruption_check be DistributedMemory.verify_data_integrity with pointer as distributed_pointer
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (not corruption_check.is_consistent) and message as "Corruption should be detected"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (corruption_check.corrupted_replicas.length is greater than 0) and message as "Corrupted replicas should be identified"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: Integration Tests

Process called "test_end_to_end_distributed_workflow" returns Boolean:
    Let distributed_context be DistributedMemory.create_distributed_context with config as DistributedMemory.default_config
    
    Note: Setup complete distributed cluster
    For i from 1 to TEST_NODE_COUNT:
        Let node be create_mock_distributed_node with node_id as i.to_string()
        DistributedMemory.join_cluster with context as distributed_context and node as node
    
    Note: Allocate distributed memory
    Let allocation_request be DistributedMemory.AllocationRequest with:
        size as 1024
        replication_level as 2
        consistency_level as "strong"
        
    Let distributed_pointer be DistributedMemory.allocate_distributed with context as distributed_context and request as allocation_request
    
    Note: Write and read data
    Let test_data be "end_to_end_test_data"
    Let write_result be DistributedMemory.write_distributed with pointer as distributed_pointer and data as test_data
    Let read_result be DistributedMemory.read_distributed with pointer as distributed_pointer
    
    Note: Perform distributed operations
    Let lock be DistributedMemory.acquire_distributed_lock with context as distributed_context and lock_id as "e2e_lock" and timeout_ms as 1000
    
    Note: Trigger garbage collection
    Let gc_result be DistributedMemory.trigger_distributed_gc with context as distributed_context
    
    Note: Free memory
    Let free_result be DistributedMemory.free_distributed with context as distributed_context and pointer as distributed_pointer
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as distributed_pointer and message as "Distributed allocation should succeed"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as write_result and message as "Distributed write should succeed"
    Let result3 be assert_equal with actual as read_result and expected as test_data and message as "Distributed read should return correct data"
    Let result4 be assert_not_null with value as lock and message as "Distributed lock should be acquired"
    Let result5 be assert_true with condition as gc_result.success and message as "Distributed GC should succeed"
    Let result6 be assert_true with condition as free_result and message as "Distributed free should succeed"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6

Note: Test Runner

Process called "run_all_distributed_memory_tests" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Display "Starting Distributed Memory comprehensive test suite..."
    
    Note: Context and Cluster Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_create_distributed_context" and test_function as test_create_distributed_context
    run_test with test_name as "test_join_distributed_cluster" and test_function as test_join_distributed_cluster
    
    Note: Distributed Allocation Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_distributed_memory_allocation" and test_function as test_distributed_memory_allocation
    run_test with test_name as "test_distributed_memory_replication" and test_function as test_distributed_memory_replication
    
    Note: Synchronization Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_distributed_memory_consistency" and test_function as test_distributed_memory_consistency
    run_test with test_name as "test_distributed_locking" and test_function as test_distributed_locking
    
    Note: Fault Tolerance Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_node_failure_handling" and test_function as test_node_failure_handling
    run_test with test_name as "test_distributed_garbage_collection" and test_function as test_distributed_garbage_collection
    
    Note: Performance Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_distributed_allocation_performance" and test_function as test_distributed_allocation_performance
    run_test with test_name as "test_network_communication_performance" and test_function as test_network_communication_performance
    
    Note: Security Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_distributed_access_control" and test_function as test_distributed_access_control
    
    Note: Error Handling Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_network_partition_handling" and test_function as test_network_partition_handling
    run_test with test_name as "test_distributed_memory_corruption_detection" and test_function as test_distributed_memory_corruption_detection
    
    Note: Integration Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_end_to_end_distributed_workflow" and test_function as test_end_to_end_distributed_workflow
    
    Display "Distributed Memory test suite completed."
    Display "Results: " plus passed_count plus " passed, " plus failed_count plus " failed, " plus test_count plus " total"
    
    Return Dictionary[String, Any] with:
        "total_tests" as test_count
        "passed_tests" as passed_count
        "failed_tests" as failed_count
        "success_rate" as (passed_count divided by test_count)
        "test_results" as test_results

Note: Main execution
Process called "main":
    Let results be run_all_distributed_memory_tests()
    Return results

Note: Execute tests when module is run
Let main_result be main()